full_threads.body:
Hi Martina, 

Ok regarding the stats, I don't have access to Google Analytics, but, I can see that from the 1 Jan to 30 Mar 2020 the survey from received 38 responses. So if you divide 38 by the number of unique visitors across the same date range you will have your conversion rate. 

E.g. if there were 1200 visitors = 38/1200*100 = 3.167%

I will get back to you on the other part of your query soon.

Thank you very much Heath for your quick response.

Here are the login details:

Hi Martina, 

I have had a look at this and it looks as though Radar setup the responses to flow into JotForm? Do you have logins for that platform? We can have a look in there and determine if there are any analytics and if we can setup more forms for you.

Hi Heath

I hope all is well in your world.

Could you please advise what the rate is of visitors to our website filling in the popup survey?

Also could you please advise whether it is possible to add a button with a link to https://royalrehab.com.au/about-us/foundation/how-to-donate at the bottom of this survey & whether this survey can be programmed so that it only pops up on webpages not related to our Private Hospital. At this stage please do not go ahead and make any changes - I just wanted to find out whether this was possible.

Finally, do you have any suggestions on how a donate button could pop up on our website apart from the one which is fixed in our header.

Thanks very much Heath and take care.

Hi Martina,

Happy for you to liaise with Health on this. Please keep me cc'd in so I am across the suggestions and can sign off any changes to the site.

It's important that we do a Foundation pop up in a way that is appealing to visitors and we need to be conscious of how often we are asking individuals so as not to annoy. We can limit the number of times a pop up appears based in IP addresses. Or perhaps it appears on certain pages where the visitors are more likely to feel like donating such as the BIU and SIU as opposed to the Private Hospital where it's not really appropriate to be asking.

Health may have alternative ideas.
